Effective, January 27, 1972. Subject to change without notice. Local times.
F = First Class — Y = Economy Class — OW = One Way — RT = Round Trip — EX = Excursion
LV = Leaving - AR = Arriving
B = Breakfast - L = Lunch - S = Snack - D = Dinner
*As of April 1, 1972 fares will be revised.
+ Arrives following day
TRAVEL DOCUMENTS REQUIRED: U.S. citizens for Colombia, proof of citizenship,
2 passport photos for Tourist Card (no charge) from Consulate or Avianca. For
other countries and other nationalities contact your Avianca office.
CUSTOMS REGULATIONS: For Colombia you may bring in 2 bottles of liquor for
personal consumption; 200 cigarettes or 50 cigars. No currency restrictions. For
other countries contact your Avianca office.
DAILY FLIGHTS within Colombia via Avianca - from Bogota to all key cities. High
frequency service to Cali, Medellin, Barranquilla, Cartagena, Bucaramanga, Santa
Marta, san Andres.
THE COLOMBIAN INTERNATIONAL AIRLINE
Avianca
